  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A growing interest in monitoring cardiac output (CO) non-invasively has emerged, however its
      determination has been difficult using the standard approaches. The aim of the study is to
      evaluate the accuracy and precision of pulse contour analysis (PCA) as compared to cardiac
      magnetic resonance imaging (CMR).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
